SIMPLE: brownout
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: brownout
<hw>brown"out</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>darkness resulting
from the extinction of lights (as in a city invisible to enemy
aircraft).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> blackout, dimout.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a partial reduction in the amount of electric power
available to customers in a region, such as by reduction of voltage or
selective cutoff of certain customers; -- it occurs for example in
summer when the demand for electricity for air-conditioning exceeds the
supply, or when power to certain customers is cut off by a severe storm.
It is contrasted with <contr>blackout</contr>, which is the total loss
of electrical power in a region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brownness</ent>⟦br⟧
